Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.42,0:00:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,No longer needed?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.26,0:00:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean by that, Mr. Schuwald?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.89,0:00:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm saying that the investigation\NI asked you to do is now over.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.81,0:00:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold on a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.60,0:00:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, the investigation\Non Karl Neuman is done.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.48,0:00:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,He was your son.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.27,0:00:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You have my gratitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.36,0:00:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, hold on.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.11,0:00:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That doesn't mean everything is resolved.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.82,0:00:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a possibility\Nthat Edmund Fahren did not die by suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.58,0:00:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't know\Nwho was pulling the strings behind Fahren.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.50,0:00:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything has been resolved.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.67,0:00:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The tea is ready, Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.64,0:00:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.39,0:00:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.48,0:01:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you like some too?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.27,0:01:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no, I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.36,0:01:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.94,0:01:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Send me your bill.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.28,0:01:10.61,Default,,0,0,0,,What nice weather today.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.11,0:01:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.62,0:01:13.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Johan is here too.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.08,0:01:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. Johan is also here?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.29,0:01:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Can a cold-hearted man who trusts no one\Nand keeps everyone at a distance
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.84,0:01:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,transform into a good-natured old man\Njust from finding his son?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.60,0:01:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That smile…
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.60,0:01:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hard to believe that man\Nwas called the Vampire of Bavaria.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.48,0:01:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,"I see. Johan is also here?" Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.62,0:03:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So, now you're running around\Nlooking for this puppy, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.88,0:03:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it seems my client's ex-husband\Ntook off with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.80,0:03:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like custody disputes over puppies\Ncan be difficult too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.76,0:03:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Good grief.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.06,0:03:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, but I'm going to have some wine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.68,0:03:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Go right ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.39,0:03:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Water is enough for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.15,0:03:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You say work has slowed down,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.19,0:03:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,but you also\Ndon't seem tempted by alcohol.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.07,0:03:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it's all okay on that front.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.41,0:04:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,On that front?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.53,0:04:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there something else\Nbothering you then?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.41,0:04:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I have some free time,\Nso I end up doing stupid things.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.37,0:04:09.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.42,0:04:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I end up looking at personal scrapbooks\NI made in my police detective days.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.42,0:04:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,About unsolved cases.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.42,0:04:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.38,0:04:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And how do you feel when you look at them?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.18,0:04:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Frustrated.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.47,0:04:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,With those murder cases and this one,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.10,0:04:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,when I think about how those criminals\Nare living comfortably in this world,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.36,0:04:35.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I just can't bear how incapable I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.07,0:04:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You were capable.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.32,0:04:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But Richard, you'd get\Ntoo caught up in your cases
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.45,0:04:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and identify too much with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.62,0:04:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd get frustrated that you couldn't see\Nwhat the culprit was thinking…
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.17,0:04:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So I ran to alcohol.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.17,0:04:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.38,0:04:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.67,0:04:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, here's our food.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.64,0:05:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,But I don't think it's a bad thing
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.81,0:05:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that you look at scrapbooks\Nfrom your old cases.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.65,0:05:13.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It just makes me more frustrated.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.65,0:05:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's fine now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.36,0:05:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me what thoughts you have when you\Nsee them from your current perspective.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.16,0:05:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You were drunk\Nand killed that young serial killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.79,0:05:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You are ready now\Nto face that truth head on.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.04,0:05:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,But you are still running away from
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.25,0:05:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,remembering the thoughts you had\Nwhen you pulled the trigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.63,0:05:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You still see it, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.59,0:05:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,That young man's ghost.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.85,0:05:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.52,0:05:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,When you make everything clear\Nand bring it all into the light,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.19,0:05:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that ghost will disappear as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.85,0:06:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,"Bring it all into the light," huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.02,0:06:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The Murder Case of Holmer the Accountant.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.52,0:06:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The victim, Joachim Holmer,\Nhad built a steady career,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.36,0:06:46.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and was not someone\Nwho would incur anyone's wrath.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.49,0:06:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet he was stabbed repeatedly\Nand nothing was even stolen.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.00,0:06:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The "Voice of God" Murder Case.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.46,0:06:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The victims were\Na former maid and chauffeur.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.92,0:07:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,On the wall of both crime scenes,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.26,0:07:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,the culprit scribbled a message.\N"I heard the voice of God."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.26,0:07:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The Dornach CEO Murder Case.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.10,0:07:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Ruud Gauck,\Na prominent person of wealth in Bavaria,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.35,0:07:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,was found dead in Hart-Holz forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.19,0:07:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The Spieler Couple Murder Case.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.82,0:07:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,A drowned middle-aged couple were found\Nfloating in the upper Isar River.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.53,0:07:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It is being investigated as one\Nof the middle-aged couple serial murders.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.45,0:07:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The suspect, a Japanese doctor,\Nis still at large.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.54,0:07:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What a mess.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.38,0:07:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,As the unsolved cases grew in number,\Nso did my alcohol intake.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.13,0:07:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,But now I'm different from back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.51,0:07:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. It's as the doctor said.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.06,0:07:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is what he meant by\Nthinking without drinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.73,0:08:01.65,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.32,0:08:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold on a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.32,0:08:05.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Think carefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.24,0:08:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Think care--
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.27,0:08:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.19,0:08:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,What was it that you remembered then?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.61,0:08:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's the thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.15,0:08:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Something did come to mind, but…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.40,0:08:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You saw that young man's ghost\Nand your flash of inspiration vanished?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.58,0:08:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.91,0:08:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You needn't rush this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.00,0:09:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That flash of inspiration\Nwill come to you again soon enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.13,0:09:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What was it that came to mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.84,0:09:14.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It felt like an important key\Nto solving one of the unsolved cases.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.35,0:09:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Just my imagination.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.41,0:09:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's there?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.45,0:09:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's there? Who's following me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.09,0:09:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just like back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.59,0:09:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Back then, I was chasing him down\Nin an alley like this…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.61,0:10:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry for visiting at this hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.86,0:10:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you're ready to talk about everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.49,0:10:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.04,0:10:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,At that moment,\NI could see inside that young man.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.58,0:10:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I learned that it existed in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.25,0:10:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,True evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.71,0:10:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.47,0:10:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I shot down that young man.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.76,0:10:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Good, you did well in telling me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.35,0:10:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,With this, you've really recovered.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.98,0:10:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,There's more.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.56,0:10:46.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized something.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.77,0:10:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.40,0:10:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,What came to mind earlier…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.40,0:10:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,All those unsolved cases\Nthat I had were actually
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.78,0:10:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,just one case.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.08,0:11:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,"Dear Dr. Gillen."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.54,0:11:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,"The book you sent me, Theory of\NTranscendent Criminal Psychology,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.88,0:11:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,was a fascinating read."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.72,0:11:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,"I feel great joy\Nin knowing that a pupil I taught
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.64,0:11:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,at  the University of Düsseldorf\Nis actively working like this."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.35,0:11:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,"By the way, Dr. Gillen,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.19,0:11:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,in your interviews with Peter Jürgens,\Nthe serial killer you mentioned,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.57,0:11:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe he told you 
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.66,0:11:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that he was ordered\Nby a friend to commit the murder."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.71,0:11:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,"My memory is unclear,\Nso could you please tell me once more
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.59,0:11:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,the name of Jürgens's friend?"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.22,0:12:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,"P.S."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.81,0:12:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,"You were an incredibly brilliant student\Nduring your college years,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.06,0:12:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,but you had a classmate
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.69,0:12:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,who was brilliant enough\Nto compete with you for the top rank."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.57,0:12:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,"He continued on\Nthe path of becoming a brain surgeon,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.65,0:12:19.99,Default,,0,0,0,,but now he is the suspect\Nof a serial murder case."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.82,0:12:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,"Can you tell me whatever you know\Nabout him, however small it may be?"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.70,0:12:27.99,Default,,0,0,0,,"What kind of person is he,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.58,0:12:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and where is he now?"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.63,0:12:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,"The man named Dr. Tenma."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.97,0:12:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you're the police detective\Nfrom back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.84,0:12:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, now I'm a private investigator\Ndoing a variety of work.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.26,0:12:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I apologize for bringing up\Nsuch a tough topic,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.85,0:12:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,but may I ask you one more time
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.44,0:12:52.99,Default,,0,0,0,,about the "Voice of God" Case\Nwhere your mother was a victim?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.07,0:12:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.90,0:12:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, it has already been four years,\Nand the police are no longer trying.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.03,0:13:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Schuwald?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.53,0:13:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.62,0:13:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe your mother was a housekeeper\Nfor that wealthy individual.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.00,0:13:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, but that was 20 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.63,0:13:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Was there a reason why she quit?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.30,0:13:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,She wasn't in great health at the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.26,0:13:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and she'd only take jobs\Nin the neighborhood after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.30,0:13:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Could it be that things\Ndidn't go well with Mr. Schuwald?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.02,0:13:28.27,Default,,0,0,0,,That's unthinkable.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.35,0:13:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, she loved to read poems.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.48,0:13:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,She said when Mr. Schuwald\Ncould still see,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.27,0:13:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,they'd often read aloud together.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.99,0:13:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, right. Please come this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.95,0:13:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,See? Take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.04,0:13:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I've kept them,\Nas they're memories of my mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.21,0:13:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,All of these poetry anthologies
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.38,0:13:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,were presents she received\Nfrom Mr. Schuwald.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.68,0:14:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The ex-detective who was on\Nthe Dornach CEO Murder Case
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.80,0:14:07.97,Default,,0,0,0,,is now a private investigator, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.64,0:14:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to speak once more with you,\Nthe CEO's former secretary,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.85,0:14:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,about people who resented your CEO.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.56,0:14:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The CEO's enemies?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.03,0:14:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you there'd be no end\Nif I started listing them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.15,0:14:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The list of companies that went bankrupt\Nbecause of the CEO, Mr. Gauck,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.45,0:14:28.37,Default,,0,0,0,,should already have been analyzed\Nby the police long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.45,0:14:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,There is one more influential\Nwealthy individual in Bavaria, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.54,0:14:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,What was his relationship with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.83,0:14:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you mean Mr. Schuwald?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.38,0:14:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, of course,\Nthey were life-long rivals.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.55,0:14:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you aware?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.30,0:14:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Of what?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.51,0:14:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Schuwald has gone bankrupt\Ntwice in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.81,0:14:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The second time was the result
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.56,0:14:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,of fierce business competition\Nwith Mr. Gauck.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.31,0:15:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words,\Nyour CEO put Mr. Schuwald out of business.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.07,0:15:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,But Schuwald has also\Nput our CEO under before too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.11,0:15:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Did they despise each other?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.20,0:15:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.91,0:15:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,There'd be trouble when the two met\Noccasionally at party venues,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.62,0:15:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,baring their emotions\Nas they'd quarrel with each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.71,0:15:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Those two did that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.09,0:15:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, despite their cold nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.71,0:15:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,They could argue with nobody\Non an equal footing but each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.51,0:15:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather than rivals,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.68,0:15:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,they were actually more like friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.83,0:15:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Careful up there!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.76,0:16:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, he knew Hans very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.43,0:16:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,He was one of the two people\Nkilled in the "Voice of God" Case.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.51,0:16:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,He was a good guy too.\NI feel sorry for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.27,0:16:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Was Hans really that nice?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.69,0:16:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, he'd treat him to drinks often.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.69,0:16:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,He used to work\Nas Schuwald's chauffeur, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.45,0:16:31.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Apparently.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.58,0:16:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But that was 30 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.20,0:16:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know why he was fired?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.58,0:16:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because Schuwald\Nwent bankrupt around then.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.13,0:16:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.54,0:16:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's not like\Nthere were any other issues?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.63,0:16:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.63,0:16:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm saying this to protect Hans's honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.97,0:16:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It didn't matter if you were\Na rich bastard or a poor person like us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.31,0:16:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,He was a good guy who'd hang out with you\Nno matter who you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.48,0:17:01.02,Default,,0,0,0,,He'd often say
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.10,0:17:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,that he was the one who taught\Nthe rich guy how to birdwatch.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.53,0:17:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Birdwatch?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.03,0:17:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. He may be called a vampire,\Nbut when he took him to the woods,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.66,0:17:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,he'd get excited like a little boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.99,0:17:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Two years have already passed,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.75,0:17:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,yet whenever I think of\Nmy husband, I still…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.88,0:17:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,My husband was an earnest man.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.29,0:17:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no reason\Npeople would hold a grudge against him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.67,0:17:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet he was killed in such a manner…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.93,0:17:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I can only imagine.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.01,0:17:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I apologize,\Nbut I believe your husband was…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.31,0:17:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, he was in an orphanage as a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.39,0:17:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,He moved from one foster home to another
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.94,0:17:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and became an accountant\Nafter all that hardship.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.77,0:17:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Schuwald asked him to work\Nas his accountant, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.65,0:17:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, many times.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.91,0:17:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,But he would refuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.28,0:17:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Not only was he busy with the work he had,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.91,0:18:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,but he said his philosophy regarding money\Nwas different from his own.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.13,0:18:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,My husband was adamant\Nthat the money be clean.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.38,0:18:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for your cooperation.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.88,0:18:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Will the culprit be caught?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.51,0:18:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll do my best.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.39,0:18:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I will catch him no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.76,0:18:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.77,0:18:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,-Oh, by the way…\N-Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.02,0:18:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know how your husband met him?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.73,0:18:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, he said they met in the woods.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.24,0:18:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,In the woods?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.03,0:18:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It was when Mr. Schuwald could still see.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.20,0:18:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,He ran into him in the woods.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.99,0:18:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Why was it in a place like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.50,0:18:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,They were birdwatching.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.46,0:18:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,They met many times after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.68,0:18:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Birdwatching…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.22,0:18:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Excited like a little boy…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.68,0:19:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,They'd read aloud together…
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.77,0:19:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Friends…
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.15,0:19:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you okay?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.07,0:19:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I'm fine. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.74,0:19:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What awful driving.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.95,0:19:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It almost looked like\Nhe was trying to hit you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.38,0:19:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Reichwein,\NI've collected all the evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.09,0:19:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It was exactly as I told you\Nthe other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.05,0:19:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The many cases I had\Nwhen I was a police detective
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.01,0:19:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,were all pointing in the same direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.31,0:19:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The "Voice of God" Murder Case.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.61,0:19:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The Dornach CEO Murder Case.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.44,0:19:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The Accountant Murder Case.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.86,0:19:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,At first glance,\Nthese cases seem unrelated to each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.07,0:19:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The modus operandi are all different too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.53,0:20:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The victims aren't connected
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.95,0:20:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and they're not related monetarily\Nin any way either.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.33,0:20:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus, there was one truth\Nthat didn't exist on record.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.54,0:20:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,There was one point\Nthat connected them all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.01,0:20:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Each victim's death
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.88,0:20:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,forced Schuwald into solitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.56,0:20:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And there was\None more strange commonality.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.69,0:20:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,In the Dornach CEO Murder Case,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.69,0:20:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,right before the crime,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.48,0:20:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Gauck left, saying he was going\Nto an important business meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.32,0:20:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The name of the person he was to meet,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.70,0:20:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and the name of the god written on\Nthe walls in the "Voice of God" Case.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.20,0:20:44.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And the middle-aged couple serial murder,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.04,0:20:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,the only case that seemed unrelated\Nto the other cases I had.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.21,0:20:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The culprit's name that was stated\Nduring the investigation by a suspect,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.09,0:20:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the Japanese doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.42,0:20:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,They were all the same name.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.51,0:20:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Johan.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.93,0:21:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,A former pupil of mine,\Na criminal psychologist,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.39,0:21:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,was researching a serial killer\Nwho was ordered by a friend to kill.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.81,0:21:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,He told me of this in his letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.40,0:21:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The name of that friend was also
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.78,0:21:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Johan.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.41,0:21:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a common name.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.62,0:21:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The connection between the cases\Nis nothing more than a guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.62,0:21:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,But if this is indeed the truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.71,0:21:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,it would mean this Johan\Nstrategically committed serial murders
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.79,0:21:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,for the past four years\Nto push Schuwald into total isolation.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.63,0:21:46.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And Margot Langer, the one who birthed\NSchuwald's son, is conveniently dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.26,0:21:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The student, Fahren,\Nwho claimed to be Schuwald's son,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.69,0:21:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,conveniently killed himself\Nwhen the real son appeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.77,0:21:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,If he really does exist,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.15,0:22:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,where is this Johan now?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.12,0:22:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. Johan is also here?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.04,0:22:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi, Johan.\NWhat lovely weather we have today.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.96,0:22:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it's very nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.76,0:22:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,He's right next to Schuwald.
